The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for MR image reconstruction from undersampled measurements. Specifically, it uses unsupervised deep learning (variational autoencoders) to learn the probability distribution of fully sampled MR images and uses this as an explicit prior term in reconstruction. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of prior knowledge and information theory, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which could also place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
